# Windows shell execution (agents)

Cursor on this machine may run **PowerShell** even when commands look like bash. Repo root: `C:\Projects\proxmox` (Git Bash: `/c/Projects/proxmox`, WSL: `/mnt/c/Projects/proxmox`).

## When to use which approach

- **Simple Docker Compose** (no pipes, no `$()`, no HEREDOC): set Shell tool `working_directory` to `C:\Projects\proxmox` and run `docker compose …` directly.
- **Everything else** (pipes, `head`/`grep`, `$(pwd)`, `scripts/*.sh`, git HEREDOC): wrap in `bash -lc '…'` or run inside WSL/Docker.

## Path rules

| Context | Format | Example |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Shell tool `working_directory` | Windows backslashes OK | `C:\Projects\proxmox` |
| Docker `-v` from Windows host | Git Bash / Docker Desktop style | `"/c/Projects/proxmox:/work"` |
| Inside WSL bash (`bash -lc`) | WSL mount path | `/mnt/c/Projects/proxmox` |
| Inside Git Bash | MSYS path | `/c/Projects/proxmox` |

Never use `C:\…` backslashes inside Docker volume strings.

## Anti-patterns

| Avoid (PowerShell) | Use instead |
|--------------------|-------------|
| `Select-Object -First N` | `bash -lc '… \| head -n N'` |
| `Select-String -Pattern` | `bash -lc '… \| grep pattern'` |
| `$env:VAR` / backtick continuations | `export VAR=…` inside `bash -lc` |
| `cat <<'EOF'` for git commits | Full commit wrapped in `bash -lc '…'` |
| `C:\Projects\…` in `docker -v` | `"/c/Projects/…"` |

## On failure

Retry once with `bash -lc` and POSIX paths before changing command logic.
